attachments.title: Obama’s Female Staffers Made Sure Their Voices Were Heard With a Genius Strategy
attachments.fallback: The Cut: Obama’s Female Staffers Made Sure Their Voices Were Heard With a Genius Strategy

text: not sure if this was shared already, but i love this concept
oh wow. this is awesome. thanks for sharing!!!!!

yeah so good (and you will see me trying to do this more!) _Female staffers adopted a meeting strategy they called “amplification”: When a woman made a key point, other women would repeat it, giving credit to its author. This forced the men in the room to recognize the contribution — and denied them the chance to claim the idea as their own._ :trophy:
thannks <@U13GPDA1F> - love to see a successful model for women supporting one another

the event itself looks interesting, but I’m also interested in their trained facilitator running the event. I wonder what that training looks like, and how other people could get trained in this type of facilitation
